Solving Quadratic Equations
search_results.snippet: To solve a quadratic equation ax² + bx + c = 0, use the quadratic formula: x = (-b ± √(b² - 4ac)) / 2a.

search_results.title: Systems of Linear Equations
search_results.snippet: A system of linear equations can be solved using substitution, elimination, or matrix methods. For a system of two equations with two unknowns, the solution is the intersection point.

search_results.title: Limits
search_results.snippet: The limit of a function f(x) as x approaches a value c is the value that f(x) gets arbitrarily close to as x gets arbitrarily close to c.
